	<div class="panel panel-primary">
		<div class="panel-heading">User Guide</div>
		<div class="panel-body">
				<div class="second-paragraph">
				Welcome to the Disinformation Fighting System User Guide. This guide will accompany you in the navigation process through the various components of the website, offering you a complete overview of the system's functions and methods of use.
				</div>
				<br>
				<div class="first-paragraph"> HOME</div>
				<div>
				The welcome page will give you a general introduction to the "Disinformation Fighting System". Here you can find information about its purpose, the benefits it offers and its main features. The Home page is the starting point for further exploring the site.
				</div>
				<br>
				<div class="first-paragraph"> SOURCE AND NEWS</div>
				<div>
				By accessing the "Source and News" section, you will be able to view two important lists: the blacklist and the whitelist of news publication sources. The blacklist includes sources that you consider untrustworthy, while the whitelist contains those that you consider trustworthy. Through the links on the page, you can examine both lists. In addition, you will have access to news that has already been analyzed by the system. You can use the dedicated links to view detailed analyzes of these news stories.
				</div>
				<br>
				<div class="first-paragraph"> HELP</div>
				<div>
				The "Help" section will provide you with valuable information on the policy adopted by the "Disinformation Fighting System" for news analysis. You will better understand the methodologies and algorithms used to evaluate the reliability of news. In addition, you will find a list of key requirements that you should consider when reading a news story to evaluate its reliability. In the "Help" section you will also have the possibility to access this same User Guide, which will provide you with detailed instructions on how to use the system.
				</div>
				<br>
				<div class="first-paragraph"> MODERATOR</div>
				<div>
				The "Moderator" section is dedicated to those who wish to take on the role of moderator in the "Disinformation Fighting System". If you are a basic user interested in becoming a moderator, you can register by clicking on the "Register" button on the page. You will be redirected to a registration form where you can provide the necessary information. If you are already a registered moderator, you will be able to log in by clicking on the "Login" button which will take you to the login form. Once logged in as a moderator, you'll have access to exclusive features, such as viewing user feedback on news analytics. Furthermore, on the page you will find a short description that clarifies the meaning and responsibilities of the role of moderator.
				</div>
				<br>
				<div class="first-paragraph"> ANALYSIS</div>
				<div>
				The "Analysis" section will allow you to submit a link to a news item that you wish the system to analyze. Once the link has been inserted, the system will proceed with the analysis and provide the result, represented by the reliability index of the news. You will then be able to evaluate the reliability of the news based on the index provided. Furthermore, you will have the possibility to provide feedback on the result of the analysis carried out by the system, thus contributing to continuously improve the accuracy and effectiveness of the system itself.
				</div>
